        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Douthat State Park, or near Clifton Forge, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clifton Forge...
Warm Springs...
Hot Springs...
Iron Gate...
Lake Moomaw...
Douthat State Park...
and Natural Well.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
